                            <comment id="90424" author="yong.fan" created="Wed, 30 Jul 2014 05:35:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Similar as &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5209&quot; title=&quot;sanity-lfsck test_18d failure: Expect file2 size 4, but got 0&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5209&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5209&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, the former failed test_18c left some dirty environment, and caused the test files had non-initialised PFID xattr, as to the subsequent LFSCK used new FID for the orphan OST-object&apos;s parent, that is not the expected result.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;So it is the side effect of failed test_18c for &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-5208&quot; title=&quot;sanity-lfsck test_18c failure: Expect 3 fixed on mds1, but got: 2&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-5208&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-5208&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
